The paper discusses a new way of analyzing algorithms, which is related to computational complexity theory. Therefore, cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses problems related to optimization, graph coloring, and satisfiability, which are typical topics in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CG (Computational Geometry). The paper also mentions tiling, which is a topic in cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). Finally, the paper discusses hardness results, which are related to cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
